description: BusyBox v1.01 (2016.02.01-08:48+0000) - A multi-purpose toolset commonly used in embedded systems, containing simplified implementations of various Unix utilities. While no directly matching vulnerabilities were found in NVD, it is recommended to check for available patches or security advisories specific to this version.

OpenSSL 1.0.0g (18 Jan 2012) - This is an older version of OpenSSL known to contain multiple vulnerabilities, including the Heartbleed vulnerability (CVE-2014-0160). It is strongly recommended to upgrade to the latest version.

uClibc dynamic linker - Although the exact version number was not found, the filename /lib/ld-uClibc.so.0 confirms the use of uClibc C library. Further analysis is required to determine the specific version.
GCC compiler version - Two GCC version strings were found: 3.3.2 and 4.5.3, indicating that the firmware may have been compiled using different versions of GCC.
